    <h3>2. RDFa and RDF: WTF?</h3>
    <p>
      RDFa it's not the same thing of RDF. They're different because (pode usar "The difference is because) RDF is just a data model designed for the Web and it serves for specify relations. RDFa is how you can describe RDF relations in your HTML code (<a href="http://manu.sporny.org/2012/mythical-differences/">Read why it's better than microformats!</a>)
Some concepts of RDFa are important:
    </p>

    <p>
      Remember that you will always have a triple: a described relation between objects.
    </p>

    <p>
      The @prefix, that is an <http="http://www.w3.org/TeamSubmission/turtle/">turtle</a> expression, serves to declare the abreviation of the URI, specified by a <a href="http://www.w3.org/blog/data/2014/01/06/vocabularies-at-w3c/">vocabulary</a> described by RDF triples in a single domain. Vocabularies defines what triple means, because it allows desambiguation.
    </p>

    <p>
      RDFa lite is a simple version of <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/rdfa-primer/">RDFa Primer</a> and it's used to describe RFD to browsers. You can read the documentation of RDFa Lite at W3C's <a http="http://www.w3.org/TR/rdfa-lite/">docs</a>.
    </p>

    <p>
      RDFa uses basically:
      <br/>
      Atribute: vocab, typeof, property, resource, prefix.
      <br />
      See this example, from W3C RDFa Lite docs:

      <pre><code class="language-markup">
        <%=h '<p vocab="http://schema.org/" typeof="Person">
           My name is
           <span property="name">Manu Sporny</span>
           and you can give me a ring via
           <span property="telephone">1-800-555-0199</span>
           or visit
           <a property="url" href="http://manu.sporny.org/">my homepage</a>.
        </p>' %>
      </code></pre>
      <br />
      and Resource:
      <br />
      See this example, from W3C RDFa Lite docs:
      <pre><code class="language-markup">
  <%=h '<p vocab="http://schema.org/" resource="#manu" typeof="Person">
       My name is
       <span property="name">Manu Sporny</span>
       and you can give me a ring via
       <span property="telephone">1-800-555-0199</span>.
       <img property="image" src="http://manu.sporny.org/images/manu.png" />
  </p>' %>
      </code></pre>
      <br />
      Another example:
      <pre><code class="language-markup">
        <%=h '<div vocab="http://schema.org/" typeof="Product">
          <img property="image" src="droid.jpg" />
          <span property="name">Android Phone</span>
        </div>' %>
      </code></pre>
      <br/>
      This example describes the subject of the picture, using RDFa triples.
